<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,260,551]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,454,479]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks:</emphasis>
A species with a very disjunct distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="McInnes" box="[794,976,455,479]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refString="McInnes, S. J. (1994 a) Zoogeographic distribution of terrestrial / freshwater tardigrades from current literature. Journal of Natural History, 28, 257 - 352. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939400770131" type="journal article" year="1994" yearSuffix="a">
McInnes 
<number box="[904,963,455,479]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="1994.0">1994</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), the South American record may need verification, especially in the light of numerous recently described new 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1177,490,515]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Doryphoribius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1012,1177,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Doryphoribius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (see Degma 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
<date box="[235,361,527,551]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="2009" valueMax="2014">
<number box="[235,361,527,551]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="2011.5" valueMax="2014.0" valueMin="2009.0">2009–2014</number>
</date>
and key in Michalczyk &amp; Kaczmarek 
<number box="[794,855,527,551]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" value="2010.0">2010</number>
).
</paragraph>
